#. <section class="sutta" id="sn11.16"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn11.16:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 11"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 11"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn11.16:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn11.16:0.3"
msgid "16. Yajamānasutta"
msgstr "16. Sponsoring Sacrifice"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.16:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati gijjhakūṭe pabbate."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the Vulture’s Peak "
"Mountain."

msgctxt "sn11.16:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sakko devānamindo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""
"And then Sakka, lord of gods, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one "
"side,"

msgctxt "sn11.16:1.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho sakko devānamindo bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr "and said to him:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.16:2.1"
msgid "“Yajamānānaṃ manussānaṃ,"
msgstr "“For humans, those merit-seeking creatures,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.16:2.2"
msgid "puññapekkhāna pāṇinaṃ;"
msgstr "who sponsor sacrifices,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.16:2.3"
msgid "Karotaṃ opadhikaṃ puññaṃ,"
msgstr "making merit with attachments,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.16:2.4"
msgid "kattha dinnaṃ mahapphalan”ti."
msgstr "where is a gift very fruitful?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.501"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.16:3.1"
msgid "“Cattāro ca paṭipannā,"
msgstr "“Four practicing the path,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.16:3.2"
msgid "cattāro ca phale ṭhitā;"
msgstr "and four established in the fruit."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.16:3.3"
msgid "Esa saṅgho ujubhūto,"
msgstr "This is the upright Saṅgha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.16:3.4"
msgid "paññāsīlasamāhito."
msgstr "with wisdom, ethics, and immersion."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn11.16:4.1"
msgid "Yajamānānaṃ manussānaṃ,"
msgstr "For humans, those merit-seeking creatures,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.16:4.2"
msgid "Puññapekkhāna pāṇinaṃ;"
msgstr "who sponsor sacrifices,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.16:4.3"
msgid "Karotaṃ opadhikaṃ puññaṃ,"
msgstr "making merit with attachments,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn11.16:4.4"
msgid "Saṅghe dinnaṃ mahapphalan”ti."
msgstr "what is given to the Saṅgha is very fruitful.”"
